1
00:01:12,900 --> 00:01:19,000
<i>[Meet Yourself]</i>

2
00:01:19,000 --> 00:01:23,940
<i>[Episode 33]</i>

3
00:01:25,580 --> 00:01:31,680
<i>[Live in Abundance]</i>

4
00:01:31,680 --> 00:01:34,840
You even learned to cook?

5
00:01:34,840 --> 00:01:38,380
When you visit me during the holidays, cook for me.

6
00:01:39,280 --> 00:01:43,240
Who told you that I'm not picky? I'm a very picky eater!

7
00:01:43,840 --> 00:01:46,400
I don't care. You have to cook.

8
00:01:46,400 --> 00:01:49,520
If you won't cook for me, don't bother visiting.

9
00:01:50,400 --> 00:01:51,860
Xiao Huang!

10
00:01:51,860 --> 00:01:53,120
Uncle Deqing.

11
00:01:53,120 --> 00:01:55,500
I'm busy. I need to hang up.

12
00:01:56,960 --> 00:01:59,939
Uncle, I was just planning to speak to you about the old house today.

13
00:01:59,939 --> 00:02:02,799
Xiao Huang, I want to talk to you about the place too.

14
00:02:02,799 --> 00:02:04,580
I've thought this through.

15
00:02:04,580 --> 00:02:09,000
Our situation is unlike those well-developed areas.

16
00:02:09,000 --> 00:02:10,759
I shouldn't have requested such a high rent.

17
00:02:10,759 --> 00:02:11,719
Yes.

18
00:02:11,719 --> 00:02:13,240
When you first came here,

19
00:02:13,240 --> 00:02:15,480
I thought a young lass like you wouldn't accomplish much.

20
00:02:15,480 --> 00:02:17,120
Things are different now.

21
00:02:17,120 --> 00:02:20,800
All the villagers are like your minions.

22
00:02:20,800 --> 00:02:23,020
Minions...

23
00:02:23,020 --> 00:02:24,999
What a unique compliment!

24
00:02:24,999 --> 00:02:26,320
You're young but ambitious.

25
00:02:26,320 --> 00:02:28,900
I think you're promising. You're a great official.

26
00:02:28,900 --> 00:02:32,379
Well, I'll leave that matter in your hands.

27
00:02:32,379 --> 00:02:33,879
You can negotiate the rent.

28
00:02:33,879 --> 00:02:35,880
I'll let you decide what an appropriate rate is.

29
00:02:35,880 --> 00:02:37,520
I have complete trust in you.

30
00:02:37,520 --> 00:02:39,800
I just want to contribute to the village.

31
00:02:39,800 --> 00:02:41,540
Hold on, Uncle.

32
00:02:41,540 --> 00:02:44,179
This old estate belongs to Grandpa Yang.

33
00:02:44,180 --> 00:02:46,800
The contract also needs to be signed by Grandpa Yang.

34
00:02:46,800 --> 00:02:48,920
Our agreement doesn't matter.

35
00:02:48,920 --> 00:02:51,079
Xiao Huang, negotiate the rent.

36
00:02:51,079 --> 00:02:53,480
- I'll deal with my dad.
- That won't do.

37
00:02:53,480 --> 00:02:56,580
I can only settle the rent after you convince your dad.

38
00:02:56,580 --> 00:03:00,300
If Grandpa Yang refuses to sign the papers, my efforts will be in vain.

39
00:03:00,300 --> 00:03:01,600
I might as well work on the land allocation.

40
00:03:01,600 --> 00:03:03,639
Forget about that. There's no need for allocated land.

41
00:03:03,639 --> 00:03:05,760
I'll speak to my dad.

42
00:03:05,760 --> 00:03:09,880
Fine. I'll leave this task in your hands.

43
00:03:09,880 --> 00:03:11,380
Sure.

44
00:03:11,380 --> 00:03:14,400
Don't try to get a plot of land while I'm working hard.

45
00:03:14,400 --> 00:03:16,560
I have to be prepared for all situations. We can work on both simultaneously.

46
00:03:16,560 --> 00:03:18,300
There's no need for any preparations.

47
00:03:18,300 --> 00:03:21,020
The villagers will have opinions about the allocated land.

48
00:03:21,020 --> 00:03:23,880
Rest assured. This is no problem at all. I'll get going.

49
00:03:25,560 --> 00:03:30,200
Uncle Deqing. All the best!

50
00:03:30,200 --> 00:03:31,760
It's all in the palm of my hands.

51
00:03:31,760 --> 00:03:33,720
In your hands!

52
00:03:34,680 --> 00:03:36,640
Take care!

53
00:03:43,960 --> 00:03:46,020
Hello, Old Xie.

54
00:03:46,020 --> 00:03:47,059
Let me tell you something.

55
00:03:47,060 --> 00:03:48,759
Uncle Deqing is so frazzled.

56
00:03:48,759 --> 00:03:50,860
He came to the village committee to see me.

57
00:03:50,860 --> 00:03:52,520
I'm not lying!

58
00:03:52,520 --> 00:03:55,440
I think there's hope for this.

59
00:04:37,440 --> 00:04:39,280
Are you exercising?

60
00:04:40,000 --> 00:04:42,140
Heading to the kindergarten?

61
00:04:54,780 --> 00:04:56,700
♪ <i>You can draw the sun</i> ♪

62
00:04:56,700 --> 00:04:59,339
♪ <i>I'll draw the national flag</i> ♪

63
00:04:59,340 --> 00:05:01,980
♪ <i>Motherland, motherland</i> ♪

64
00:05:01,980 --> 00:05:04,560
♪ <i>We love you</i> ♪

65
00:05:04,560 --> 00:05:07,020
♪ <i>Motherland, motherland</i> ♪

66
00:05:07,020 --> 00:05:10,440
♪ <i>We love you</i> ♪

67
00:05:13,920 --> 00:05:15,660
Amazing!

68
00:05:15,660 --> 00:05:17,880
Kids, you sang excellently!

69
00:05:17,880 --> 00:05:20,040
During the performance, don't be nervous.

70
00:05:20,040 --> 00:05:21,800
Just sing as you usually do.

71
00:05:21,800 --> 00:05:24,820
Today, we should also thank Mr. Hu for practicing with us again.

72
00:05:24,820 --> 00:05:26,660
Let's thank Mr. Hu together.

73
00:05:26,660 --> 00:05:31,500
<i>Thank you, Mr. Hu!</i>

74
00:05:31,500 --> 00:05:34,660
You're welcome. You guys sang really well.

75
00:05:35,260 --> 00:05:37,319
Mr. Hu!

76
00:05:37,319 --> 00:05:40,140
What's wrong, Xiao Hu Lu? MInd the steps! Be careful!

77
00:05:40,140 --> 00:05:41,900
What's the matter?

78
00:05:41,900 --> 00:05:44,860
Mr. Hu, do I sing well?

79
00:05:44,860 --> 00:05:45,840
You do.

80
00:05:45,840 --> 00:05:49,040
Can I stand in the middle?

81
00:05:50,040 --> 00:05:52,880
Xiao Hu Lu, here's the thing.

82
00:05:52,880 --> 00:05:56,170
The middle spot isn't always the most important or the best.

83
00:05:56,170 --> 00:05:58,120
In a choir, everyone is important.

84
00:05:58,120 --> 00:06:00,670
Don't just think about shining alone.

85
00:06:00,679 --> 00:06:03,680
When I'm in elementary school, I won't stand in the middle.

86
00:06:03,680 --> 00:06:05,900
I can stand in the back.

87
00:06:05,900 --> 00:06:07,360
Why?

88
00:06:07,360 --> 00:06:10,379
My grandparents are coming to the performance.

89
00:06:10,380 --> 00:06:14,600
If I don't do well, my mom will be blamed.

90
00:06:14,600 --> 00:06:17,240
Your mom will be blamed?

91
00:06:17,240 --> 00:06:19,860
My grandparents think the schools here aren't good.

92
00:06:19,860 --> 00:06:22,080
They want me to go to a school in Kunming.

93
00:06:22,080 --> 00:06:23,560
I have to do well in everything.

94
00:06:23,560 --> 00:06:28,480
If I'm in the middle, my mom can let me study here.

95
00:06:29,240 --> 00:06:31,080
Is this what your mom told you?

96
00:06:31,080 --> 00:06:36,260
When Mom called Dad, I overheard them.

97
00:06:41,340 --> 00:06:44,500
Mr. Hu, help me.

98
00:06:46,840 --> 00:06:51,519
Luo Xiaoqiao! Why are you here? Class has started.

99
00:06:51,519 --> 00:06:53,780
You can go to class first. Let's talk about this later.

100
00:06:53,780 --> 00:06:57,200
What are you gripping Mr. Hu? Let's go to class.

101
00:06:57,200 --> 00:06:58,280
Goodbye, Mr. Hu.

102
00:06:58,280 --> 00:06:59,500
Goodbye.

103
00:06:59,500 --> 00:07:01,280
- Let's go.
- Listen to class.

104
00:07:39,160 --> 00:07:41,679
Na Na. Coffee.

105
00:07:41,679 --> 00:07:44,380
Okay, Mr. Hu. Give me a minute.

106
00:07:44,380 --> 00:07:48,319
Mr. Hu, I went to the bar to watch you yesterday, but you weren't at work.

107
00:07:48,319 --> 00:07:50,360
I had a day off yesterday.

108
00:07:50,360 --> 00:07:52,260
We'll go again tonight. Will you be there?

109
00:07:52,260 --> 00:07:54,560
Yeah, I will. I'll buy you a drink if you come.

110
00:07:54,560 --> 00:07:57,860
Great. It's a deal. Love you.

111
00:08:02,560 --> 00:08:06,639
Na Na, the cafe seems crowded today.

112
00:08:08,680 --> 00:08:10,640
Where's Xiaochun?

113
00:08:11,540 --> 00:08:14,700
I think she's busy with the warehouse.

114
00:08:16,000 --> 00:08:20,120
Hasn't the town been bustling lately?

115
00:08:20,120 --> 00:08:22,540
I guess so.

116
00:08:22,540 --> 00:08:24,719
I think it's because...

117
00:08:24,719 --> 00:08:28,479
that travel vlogger's video sent in the WeChat group went viral.

118
00:08:28,479 --> 00:08:31,900
People who watch that video want to come here and take a look.

119
00:08:31,900 --> 00:08:33,460
Do you think so?

120
00:08:33,460 --> 00:08:35,960
Probably.

121
00:08:37,800 --> 00:08:41,320
What's wrong? Why are you so listless?

122
00:08:41,320 --> 00:08:44,460
Look at you. Chat with me.

123
00:08:52,280 --> 00:08:54,900
Fresh cold brew tea.

124
00:08:54,900 --> 00:08:56,640
My treat.

125
00:08:59,320 --> 00:09:02,340
Why are you still treating me so coldly?

126
00:09:02,340 --> 00:09:06,360
Brother, can't you see that I'm busy?

127
00:09:06,360 --> 00:09:09,000
If you want to chat, go to Sister Manjun.

128
00:09:09,000 --> 00:09:11,120
Aren't you two dating?

129
00:09:11,120 --> 00:09:14,800
We... We aren't dating.

130
00:09:14,800 --> 00:09:18,720
We... Is this just a fling for you two?

131
00:09:19,280 --> 00:09:21,170
It's nothing!

132
00:09:21,170 --> 00:09:22,600
We're just a room apart.

133
00:09:22,600 --> 00:09:25,480
You didn't even bother being quiet.

134
00:09:29,840 --> 00:09:32,339
Do your best at work. Cheer up.

135
00:09:32,339 --> 00:09:33,400
You should get back to work.

136
00:09:33,400 --> 00:09:36,220
You... Your tumbler.

137
00:09:36,220 --> 00:09:38,760
All the best.

138
00:09:50,180 --> 00:09:51,980
<i>[Xiaochun]</i>

139
00:09:57,000 --> 00:10:00,400
<i>[Xiaochun, I want a two-week break to visit my parents in Shanghai.]</i>

140
00:10:10,620 --> 00:10:13,600
This color is gorgeous. I want to dye a skirt.

141
00:10:13,600 --> 00:10:15,319
Okay. I'll dye it for you.

142
00:10:15,319 --> 00:10:17,480
I'll dye a few more so you have a few options.

143
00:10:17,480 --> 00:10:21,199
I think the homestay's staff can wear tie-dyed clothes. What do you think?

144
00:10:21,199 --> 00:10:23,959
No problem. I'll get someone to make them for you.

145
00:10:25,080 --> 00:10:26,660
Sister!

146
00:10:26,660 --> 00:10:27,979
- Xiao Qin, are you here to hang out?
- Yeah.

147
00:10:27,980 --> 00:10:30,379
Candy!

148
00:10:30,379 --> 00:10:32,200
Uncle A'Yao.

149
00:10:32,200 --> 00:10:33,619
Sister Hongdou, you're also here.

150
00:10:33,620 --> 00:10:35,040
I'm here to help out.

151
00:10:35,040 --> 00:10:37,979
Uncle a'Yao, why is Trekking Luo Li so awesome?

152
00:10:37,979 --> 00:10:41,739
I heard Yang Zhinan say that the town's homestay is fully booked for the weekend.

153
00:10:41,739 --> 00:10:44,040
People are still calling to make reservations.

154
00:10:44,040 --> 00:10:46,360
Fully booked for the weekend?

155
00:10:46,360 --> 00:10:47,719
His homestay isn't the only fully booked spot.

156
00:10:47,719 --> 00:10:49,879
The other place in town used to charge ¥120 a night,

157
00:10:49,879 --> 00:10:52,299
but their prices have been changed to ¥220.

158
00:10:52,300 --> 00:10:53,719
That place is also fully booked.

159
00:10:53,719 --> 00:10:56,280
Is this place going to go viral?

160
00:10:56,280 --> 00:10:58,880
Uncle A'Yao, what do you need my help with?

161
00:10:58,880 --> 00:11:00,800
Hang these up.

162
00:11:00,800 --> 00:11:02,440
Okay.

163
00:11:04,220 --> 00:11:07,060
There is an evident increase in tourists lately.

164
00:11:07,060 --> 00:11:10,639
The homestays in town are fully booked for the weekend.

165
00:11:10,639 --> 00:11:15,100
Moreover, there are visitors who drive over from neighboring cities.

166
00:11:15,100 --> 00:11:18,740
We're here to discuss an emergency plan

167
00:11:18,740 --> 00:11:21,500
to get through this weekend with a tourist boom.

168
00:11:21,500 --> 00:11:23,840
We have to avoid tourists flooding this area.

169
00:11:23,840 --> 00:11:27,240
If they can't dine well or have fun, they'll leave this place upset.

170
00:11:27,240 --> 00:11:28,840
We have a village committee meeting this afternoon.

171
00:11:28,840 --> 00:11:33,000
The places visited by Luo Li in her video are definitely must-visit spots for tourists.

172
00:11:33,000 --> 00:11:34,419
So, let's make those our focus.

173
00:11:34,420 --> 00:11:36,400
For meals, that'll be Galsang Flower Restaurant.

174
00:11:36,400 --> 00:11:41,120
Be sure to notify them to prepare more ingredients and hire more temporary helpers.

175
00:11:41,120 --> 00:11:44,200
For the wood carving workshop, the cafe, the tie-dye workshop, and the embroidery workshop

176
00:11:44,200 --> 00:11:46,640
should also have sufficient manpower. We have to prepare more materials as soon as possible.

177
00:11:46,640 --> 00:11:48,479
How much is enough?

178
00:11:48,479 --> 00:11:51,400
Xiao Huang will collate data on tourist numbers in the Old Town

179
00:11:51,400 --> 00:11:53,800
and other popular towns in recent years.

180
00:11:53,800 --> 00:11:57,280
She'll also gather the reservation numbers of the homestays in the town and village.

181
00:11:57,280 --> 00:12:00,960
We'll have a preliminary estimate of the tourist flow.

182
00:12:00,960 --> 00:12:02,100
Got it.

183
00:12:02,100 --> 00:12:06,040
Actually, I'm mostly concerned about the limited capacity of our reception infrastructure.

184
00:12:06,040 --> 00:12:10,819
Exactly. When the infrastructure can't meet the customer flow,

185
00:12:10,819 --> 00:12:12,600
the service staff will never be enough.

186
00:12:12,600 --> 00:12:16,760
We can't remain in our own shoes and insist that others be considerate of us.

187
00:12:16,760 --> 00:12:20,500
Instead, we should adopt the customer's perspective and solve problems for them.

188
00:12:20,500 --> 00:12:23,680
How should we think from the perspective of customers?

189
00:12:23,680 --> 00:12:27,100
The want to be seen. They want problems to be solved.

190
00:12:27,100 --> 00:12:29,819
They want to be respected and valued.

191
00:12:29,819 --> 00:12:32,040
What exactly should we do?

192
00:12:32,040 --> 00:12:34,760
Chairman Xie and I will draft a plan.

193
00:12:34,760 --> 00:12:36,720
We may need many people.

194
00:12:36,720 --> 00:12:39,200
Let's see who has the time in the village.

195
00:12:39,200 --> 00:12:40,540
We can get them to help out.

196
00:12:40,540 --> 00:12:45,319
Okay. I'm on it. I know the villagers' schedules best.

197
00:12:45,319 --> 00:12:46,700
Okay.

198
00:12:48,240 --> 00:12:49,840
Sister Xiaochun,

199
00:12:49,840 --> 00:12:52,800
about the rest days I mentioned...

200
00:12:52,800 --> 00:12:55,580
Can you take a break after this weekend?

201
00:12:55,580 --> 00:12:57,560
We really need manpower now.

202
00:12:57,560 --> 00:13:00,660
Even Hongdou and the rest have to help out.

203
00:13:03,140 --> 00:13:06,680
- But I...
- What's the matter? Is it your parents' birthday?

204
00:13:08,080 --> 00:13:11,100
Isn't your parents' birthday in February? Right?

205
00:13:15,100 --> 00:13:18,080
I'll let you take a break next week.

206
00:13:19,380 --> 00:13:22,540
Why is everyone so on edge? Isn't this a blessing?

207
00:13:22,540 --> 00:13:26,040
We've been working hard for so long just for this day. Right?

208
00:13:26,040 --> 00:13:28,140
If we want to catch the gift of fate,

209
00:13:28,140 --> 00:13:30,820
we have to be able to bear its weight.

210
00:13:30,820 --> 00:13:32,980
Comrades, lift your spirits. Come on!

211
00:13:32,980 --> 00:13:35,739
Let's cheer each other on! Come on!

